<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"><div>===Canadian Denial===</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"><div>===Canadian Denial===</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">−</td>
  <td class="diff-deletedline"><div>{{<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">editorial</del>|<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">section</del>|<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">date</del>=<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">March</del> <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">2014</del>}}</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">+</td>
  <td class="diff-addedline"><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">In Canada, the event has been referred to as "Canada's secret battle".&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.ipolitics.ca/2013/09/18/remembering-canadas-secret-battle/ Remembering Canada’s ‘secret battle’]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://newsgroups.derkeiler.com/Archive/Soc/soc.culture.yugoslavia/2006-06/msg00026.html "Canada's secret battle – Medak Pocket"]&lt;/ref&gt; The Medak Pocket was an event that challenged the skill and discipline of an army that had not deployed formed units to fight in a full-scale battle for almost 40 years.&lt;ref name="Dallaire 2009"&gt;</ins>{{<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">cite book</ins>|<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">last=Dallaire</ins>|<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">first</ins>=<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">edited</ins> <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">by Bernd Horn ; foreword by Roméo|title=Fortune favours the brave : tales of courage and tenacity in Canadian military history|year=2009|publisher=Dundurn Press|location=Toronto|isbn=978-1-55002-841-6</ins>}}<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">&lt;/ref&gt; Military analysts have since written extensively of the effects the battle at Medak Pocket has had on the Canadian military, including the management of public information regarding the battle, and both the Canadian military's and the Canadian public's perception of what "peacekeepers" were trained to do. The battle did not gain widespread public attention in Canada at the time.&lt;ref name="Dallaire 2009"/&gt;&lt;ref name="Off 2004"/&gt;</ins></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">−</td>
  <td class="diff-deletedline"><div>In Canada, the event has been referred to as "Canada's secret battle".&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.ipolitics.ca/2013/09/18/remembering-canadas-secret-battle/ Remembering Canada’s ‘secret battle’]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://newsgroups.derkeiler.com/Archive/Soc/soc.culture.yugoslavia/2006-06/msg00026.html "Canada's secret battle – Medak Pocket"]&lt;/ref&gt; The Medak Pocket challenged the skill and discipline of the Canadian soldiers. The ability Canadians had to revert from combat soldiers to peacekeepers is a rare and highly respected standard of military practice.&lt;ref name="Dallaire 2009"&gt;{{cite book|last=Dallaire|first=edited by Bernd Horn ; foreword by Roméo|title=Fortune favours the brave : tales of courage and tenacity in Canadian military history|year=2009|publisher=Dundurn Press|location=Toronto|isbn=978-1-55002-841-6}}&lt;/ref&gt; By not telling the Canadian public about what had occurred in Medak creates a problem in two ways. The first is the effects denial has on the soldiers; a country that is ashamed of its soldiers actions will thus second guess their bravery and the value of their efforts.&lt;ref name="Dallaire 2009"/&gt;&lt;ref name="Off 2004"&gt;{{cite book|last=Off|first=Carol|title=The ghosts of Medak Pocket : the story of Canada's secret war|year=2004|publisher=Random House Canada|location=[Toronto]|isbn=0-679-31293-5}}&lt;/ref&gt; The second issue of downplaying Canadian role in Medak was the realization and fear of Canada's policy and abandonment of a "peacekeeping" heritage.&lt;ref name="Dallaire 2009"/&gt;&lt;ref name="Off 2004"/&gt; Many Canadians are unaware of the role their soldiers have in the world to restore, stabilize and change law and order in countries where it does not exist. Canadians easily can get confused with their role in other countries i.e. Afghanistan, and cannot comprehend how soldiers can be equally "warfighters, conflict negotiators and peacekeepers."&lt;ref name="Dallaire 2009"/&gt;{{POV-statement|date=December 2012}}</div></td>
  <td colspan="2" class="diff-empty">&#160;</td>
</tr>
