<li id="cite_note-CT.2FMO.2F1015e-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-CT.2FMO.2F1015e_33-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://web.archive.org/web/20080317231540/http://www.un.org/icty/pressreal/2005/p1015-e.htm">"CT/MO/1015e – RAHIM ADEMI AND MIRKO NORAC CASE TRANSFERRED TO CROATIA"</a>. pub. The Hague, 1 November 2005. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.un.org/icty/pressreal/2005/p1015-e.htm">the original</a> on 17 March 2008<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">12 August</span> 2008</span>. <q>Today, 1 November 2005, the Rahim Ademi and Mirko Norac case was officially transferred to the Republic of Croatia by the ICTY. This is the first case in which persons already indicted by the Tribunal have been referred to Croatia. It is the only case, out of 10, that the Tribunal's Prosecution has requested be transferred to Croatia.</q></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOperation+Medak+Pocket&amp;rft.btitle=CT%2FMO%2F1015e+%E2%80%93+RAHIM+ADEMI+AND+MIRKO+NORAC+CASE+TRANSFERRED+TO+CROATIA&amp;rft.date=The+Hague%2C+1+November+2005&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Ficty%2Fpressreal%2F2005%2Fp1015-e.htm&amp;rft.pub=pub&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> <span style="font-size:100%" class="error citation-comment">Check date values in: <code style="color:inherit; border:inherit; padding:inherit;">|date=</code> (<a href="/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#bad_date" title="Help:CS1 errors">help</a>)</span></span></li>
